# Documentation Refinement

Keep documentation aligned with real behavior during the same task when possible.

## Update Triggers

- Implementation changes behavior, architecture, workflow, commands, or expected outputs.
- Build/runtime/test errors expose stale, incorrect, or missing documentation.
- Actual successful process differs from documented steps (mis-implementation risk).

## Required Documentation Targets

- Update `AGENTS.md` when project map, constraints, commands, or workflow references change.
- Update related files in `docs/` when specs, decisions, guides, operations, or plans are affected.
- Update procedures in `.agents/skills/` when task instructions are incorrect, incomplete, or outdated.
- Update conflicting guidance in `.cursor/rules/` when rules cause repeated mistakes or ambiguity.

## Completion Checklist

- Confirm touched behavior has matching documentation.
- Correct source-of-truth docs instead of adding temporary notes.
- Keep edits minimal, specific, and consistent with existing structure.
- Do not finish until relevant documentation updates are complete or explicitly deferred with reason.
